Actually, you can do this by creating a custom `ConfigDataLoader` that sets the RestTemplate on the `ConfigServicePropertySourceLocator`. To do that, first create `ConfigDataLoader`;

    public class OAuth2ConfigDataLoader implements ConfigDataLoader&lt;ConfigServerConfigData&gt; {
    
        private final ConfigClientProperties clientProperties;
        private final OAuth2RestTemplate oauth2RestTemplate;
    
        public OAuth2ConfigDataLoader(ConfigClientProperties clientProperties,
                                      OAuth2RestTemplate oauth2RestTemplate) {
            this.clientProperties = clientProperties;
            this.oauth2RestTemplate = oauth2RestTemplate;
        }
    
        @Override
        public ConfigServerConfigData load(ConfigDataLoaderContext context,
                                           ConfigServerConfigDataResource resource)
                throws ConfigDataNotFoundException, IOException {
            ConfigServicePropertySourceLocator locator =
                    new ConfigServicePropertySourceLocator(clientProperties);
            locator.setRestTemplate(oauth2RestTemplate);
            return new ConfigServerConfigData(locator);
        }
    
        @Override
        public ConfigDataLoader&lt;ConfigServerConfigData&gt; withFallback(ConfigDataLoader&lt;?&gt; fallback) {
            return this;
        }
    }

Then create a configuration class to configure the `OAuth2RestTemplate`:

    @Configuration
    public class OAuth2RestTemplateConfig {
    
        @Bean
        public OAuth2RestTemplate oauth2RestTemplate() {
            // configure and return the OAuth2RestTemplate
